item.dc:creator: @Yz85Racer Yz85Racer
item.description:
@Yz85Racer wrote:

[quote=“doodooss, post:4, topic:136358”]or just do this

make a java file (Null.java) with this in it

[code]// Restart the server by rsrules - Gander pwnz me xD
import java.io.*;

public class Null
{
public void resetserver()
{
misc.println(“shutting down server”);
PlayerHandler.kickAllPlayers = true;
misc.println(“saved all player”);
closeListener();
runserver();
}
public void runserver()
{
try
{
String run = “Run.bat”;//change this to the name of your run.bat or runserver.bat(note:if u got a classfolder make a shortcut of
//run.bat and put it in the class folder
String xstr = “./”+run;
Runtime.getRuntime().exec(xstr);
}
catch (IOException ioe)
{
ioe.printStackTrace();
}
}

public void closeListener()
{
try {
server.shutdownClientHandler = true;
if(server.clientListener != null) server.clientListener.close();
server.clientListener = null;
}
catch(java.lang.Exception __ex)
{
__ex.printStackTrace();
}
}
}[/code]

and make ur runserver.bat
to run.bat[/quote]
You realise using Runtime only works for Windows don’t you?
